# Biography

Ruda Zhang is a researcher in urban transportation and smart cities. He has recently received a PhD in Civil Engineering from the University of Southern California (USC). He also has a MA in Economics from USC, and a BEng from Peking University, China. His PhD study focuses on taxi transportation, applying geospatial analysis, statistics, operations research, and game theory to billions of GPS records of taxi trips in New York City. His research interest is in designing urban transportation systems to combat traffic congestion.
